HOME | THE PREMISE | DESIGNATIONS | APP FORM | CLAIMS | SKELETONS

                                        Order born from the wrath of chaos

Chicago Illinois, a city rebuilt and protected by PRIME. It is an organization tasked with policing both the Conduit species itself and maintaining the peace between it and mankind. Having bought out the privatized contract for law enforcement throughout all of Chicago; they have kept the peace within the city. Well, for the most part. The Mavericks, a group that has seen PRIME’s methods and control have begun to rebel against the organization. They Are willing to do anything to maintain their freedom and remove PRIME from the city. They are not alone, however, and when motivations within the city collide; everyone has to pick a side, even if its the wrong one.

                                                                                          CHAOS WILL ALWAYS TRIUMPH OVER ORDER

SEQUENCE is a mutant/abilities roleplay. This group contains mature themes and is rated as such. We accept OCs and Skeleton Canon characters. We concern ourselves with our members enjoying themselves having a great place to plot, post and have fun with each other. If this sounds right up your alley, feel free to check us out and ask any questions you might have.

     Accepting within twenty four hours of receiving application!

summary: could you write like a oneshot where y/n and chris meet for the first time and there's a connection pls?
question: could you write like a oneshot where y/n and chris meet for the first time and there's a connection pls?
answer:
Hope you like it!

It was as if the cab she was on couldn’t have been going any slower. The Los Angeles traffic was probably her least favorite thing about moving to this city. Her flight was about to take off in 30 minutes and she couldn’t help but panic thinking about missing it. She promised her mom that this year she would make it to the family reunion. Her mom’s voice rang through her head, “No excuse this year Y/N! Boston misses you!”

Y/N leaned up to the cab driver and used her softest tone, “Hey bud, I can give you an extra 20 if you can speed it up. What’cha say?,” she folded a twenty lightly waving it between her fingertips and waited for his response.

Without saying a word he took the bill and nodded at her. Soon they flew through the LA roads, which would typically only spike up her anxiety. But the thought of her mom lecturing her for being late was a far worse option. The cab pulled over in front of the airport entrance and she grabbed her carry on from the trunk.

“Thanks!” she slapped her hand down on the trunk and booked it into the airport. Scanning her eyes across the list of flights on the television screen she found her flight. Flight 345 to Logan International Airport (BOS).

Y/N sped over to check in and booked it to the gate. She thanked herself for packing light, only having to roll around her small black suitcase and her tote bag around her arm. Finally reaching the gate she could finally sit down and relax. Looking down at her phone she let out a sigh of relief, made it with 5 minutes to spare. A new record for her.

The gate was getting busy and it was clear it was a flight headed to the New England area. There was of course the spare business people, those connecting through Boston, and then of course the bunch of New Englanders. They stuck out like sore thumbs in their Patriots and Celtics gear. It brought a smile to her face reminding her off how much she actually missed being home.

She kept her headphones in and went to work on beating the next level of the game on her phone. Not paying much attention she missed the intercom making flight announcements. Her head bounced up back to attention when the people around her started to huff and look angry.

Sliding off one of her headphones she turned to the man sitting next to her, “uh, excuse me, what’s going on?“

He turned to her and let out a groan, “our flight has been delayed. Something about the pilot getting sick.” He took off his black baseball cap and placed it on his lap. A set of blue eyes shined at her, “well guess we are stuck here.”

For a second she was taken back by how good looking he was. She made a note to herself to stop walking around with her eyes glued to her phone. For a moment she shuffled through everything she has done since sitting down, hoping nothing too embarrassing.

“Oh shit. Well hopefully not too long right, can’t be too bad.” Y/N shrugged her shoulders and turned a little in her seat to face him. “I’m Y/N, your new airport buddy.”

A chuckle escaped his lips and he gave her a sincere half smile, causing a dimple in his cheek to appear. “Nice to meet ya airport buddy, I’m Chris.” He bowed her head at her and laughed. “Are you headed home?”

She nodded at him in response, “Yeah a very fun family reunion,” the sarcasm was prevalent in her voice, “also known as the time to get grilled by my every living relative.”

“Hey, that could be fun!” he smiled at her and stretched his body in his seat. The man was so big and it was a bit humorous to see him hunched into the small airport seat. “I am going to see family too. A break from work.”

“And can I just say, I couldn’t help but look over… you’re never going to beat that level when you do the same move over and over again.”

She scoffed at him and let out a little laugh placing her hand on her chest. “Ouch,” Y/N looked down at her phone and grunted, “It is driving me mad to be honest. I know I am too old for phone games.”

Chris shook his head and reached into his jean back pocket to pull out his cellphone. Clicking through his messy phone screen he finally opened up same game app. “See, level 40. I can relate.”

“Just looking at how many apps you have on your phone stresses me out.” She couldn’t help but poke fun at him, “What man needs that many apps on his phone?”

“Hey hey hey! I offered to help you and here you are insulting me,” he rubbed his jaw and looked at Y/N shaking his head. “I mean I could take my phone and go somewhere more appreciated it.” Chris shrugged his shoulders and scanned his eyes around the room.

A smile swept across her lips, reaching over she shoved his shoulder lightly. “Oh stop you big baby, just teasing. Now show me how to beat this stupid game.”

Flight 345 to Logan International Airport (BOS) ready to board. The intercom rang throughout the gate lobby causing everyone to rush towards the entrance.

“Oof, I guess I am out of luck.” She stood up and threw her purse onto her shoulder. Leaning on her carry on she turned to look back at him. Chris got up and picked up a simple black duffle bag, “I think we can still make it work.”

Y/N looked at him confused, they walked over to board. He bumped his shoulder into her and whispered down at her, “How much you want to bet I can convince whoever you’re sitting with to swap seats with me?”

A light blush crept up onto her cheeks, she bit on her bottom lip and then quickly released it before answering. “Hmm… I think you can do it.” Y/N was never happier to have a delayed flight, and for picking the perfect seat in the waiting area. Her heart started to flutter as she looked at him.

Chris stepped forward and handed his passport and ticket to the flight attendant. Turning to you he grinned, “I think it’s a good thing our flight was delayed. Now I have the whole flight to school you in this game.”

Finally reaching the gate she could finally sit down and relax. Looking down at her phone she let out a sigh of relief, made it with 5 minutes to spare. A new record for her.

The gate was getting busy and it was clear it was a flight headed to the New England area. There was of course the spare business people, those connecting through Boston, and then of course the bunch of New Englanders. They stuck out like sore thumbs in their Patriots and Celtics gear. It brought a smile to her face reminding her off how much she actually missed being home.

She kept her headphones in and went to work on beating the next level of the game on her phone. Not paying much attention she missed the intercom making flight announcements. Her head bounced up back to attention when the people around her started to huff and look angry.

Sliding off one of her headphones she turned to the man sitting next to her, “uh, excuse me, what’s going on?“

He turned to her and let out a groan, “our flight has been delayed. Something about the pilot getting sick.” He took off his black baseball cap and placed it on his lap. A set of blue eyes shined at her, “well guess we are stuck here.”

For a second she was taken back by how good looking he was. She made a note to herself to stop walking around with her eyes glued to her phone. For a moment she shuffled through everything she has done since sitting down, hoping nothing too embarrassing.

“Oh shit. Well hopefully not too long right, can’t be too bad.” Y/N shrugged her shoulders and turned a little in her seat to face him. “I’m Y/N, your new airport buddy.”

A chuckle escaped his lips and he gave her a sincere half smile, causing a dimple in his cheek to appear. “Nice to meet ya airport buddy, I’m Chris.” He bowed her head at her and laughed. “Are you headed home?”

She nodded at him in response, “Yeah a very fun family reunion,” the sarcasm was prevalent in her voice, “also known as the time to get grilled by my every living relative.”

“Hey, that could be fun!” he smiled at her and stretched his body in his seat. The man was so big and it was a bit humorous to see him hunched into the small airport seat. “I am going to see family too. A break from work.”

“And can I just say, I couldn’t help but look over… you’re never going to beat that level when you do the same move over and over again.”

She scoffed at him and let out a little laugh placing her hand on her chest. “Ouch,” Y/N looked down at her phone and grunted, “It is driving me mad to be honest. I know I am too old for phone games.”

Chris shook his head and reached into his jean back pocket to pull out his cellphone. Clicking through his messy phone screen he finally opened up same game app. “See, level 40. I can relate.”

“Just looking at how many apps you have on your phone stresses me out.” She couldn’t help but poke fun at him, “What man needs that many apps on his phone?”

“Hey hey hey! I offered to help you and here you are insulting me,” he rubbed his jaw and looked at Y/N shaking his head. “I mean I could take my phone and go somewhere more appreciated it.” Chris shrugged his shoulders and scanned his eyes around the room.

A smile swept across her lips, reaching over she shoved his shoulder lightly. “Oh stop you big baby, just teasing. Now show me how to beat this stupid game.”

Flight 345 to Logan International Airport (BOS) ready to board. The intercom rang throughout the gate lobby causing everyone to rush towards the entrance.

“Oof, I guess I am out of luck.” She stood up and threw her purse onto her shoulder. Leaning on her carry on she turned to look back at him. Chris got up and picked up a simple black duffle bag, “I think we can still make it work.”

Y/N looked at him confused, they walked over to board. He bumped his shoulder into her and whispered down at her, “How much you want to bet I can convince whoever you’re sitting with to swap seats with me?”

A light blush crept up onto her cheeks, she bit on her bottom lip and then quickly released it before answering. “Hmm… I think you can do it.” Y/N was never happier to have a delayed flight, and for picking the perfect seat in the waiting area. Her heart started to flutter as she looked at him.

Chris stepped forward and handed his passport and ticket to the flight attendant. Turning to you he grinned, “I think it’s a good thing our flight was delayed. Now I have the whole flight to school you in this game.”
